ts only Windows"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":31,"created_at":"2017-09-06T00:23:17Z","updated_at":"2024-03-18T04:20:35Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"I know that this is not  the fault  of Julia,  but the Windows shell does not play nicely  with Julia in the "shell mode". For instance, typing `; dir` will result in an error because this is not a command executed by program. This applies to most of the commands available in the Windows shell. So far I found only `tree` and `help` to work...

